   $[root\_v, dist\_v] = find(v)$

2. **Case 1: $root\_u == root\_v$ (Cycle formed)**
   $u$ and $v$ are already in the same component. Adding the edge $(u, v)$ with weight $w$ creates a cycle.
   The existing path parity between $u$ and $v$ is $dist\_u \oplus dist\_v$.
   The cycle weight parity will be $(dist\_u \oplus dist\_v) \oplus w$.
   We must ensure this cycle weight is even (i.e., parity is 0).
   $dist\_u \oplus dist\_v \oplus w = 0$
   This means $w = dist\_u \oplus dist\_v$.

