   If $w \neq dist\_u \oplus dist\_v$, the cycle is odd. Reject the edge.

3. **Case 2: $root\_u \neq root\_v$ (Merging components)**
   We merge the sets, say setting $parent[root\_u] = root\_v$.
   We need to define $distance[root\_u]$, which is the parity path from $root\_u$ to $root\_v$.
   The path is $root\_u \to u \to v \to root\_v$.
